						               													<description>The ultimate &amp;quot;Who-Done-It&amp;quot; game, where 1-4 players combine human deductive reasoning with advanced computer logic to solve over 130,000 totally different murder mysteries.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Bang! Bang! Shots ring out in the big city.  A body lies alone at the docks.  The funeral dirge sounds.  19 colorful characters at the scene of the crime flee to other parts of town.  As one of the &amp;ldquo;private eyes&amp;rdquo; assigned to the case, you must interrogate these suspects.  Players compete, using logic and deduction, to be first to identify the murderer.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Features&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Each suspect card contains different questions you may ask to obtain vital information which will help you deduce the identity of the murderer.&amp;#10;     The computer becomes the suspects, as you &amp;ldquo;grill&amp;rdquo; them one by one.  You have the questions and it has the answers.  Get careless and you&amp;rsquo;ll ask for useless information.  Ask a smart question and you&amp;rsquo;ll have a key fact in a flash!&amp;#10;     Electronic Display (light-emitting diodes) shows you the answers.&amp;#10;     Your case fact sheet helps you study and weigh the suspects&amp;rsquo; statements, and logically follow the tangled web of evidence.  Now you&amp;rsquo;re ready to make an accusation.  If you&amp;rsquo;re correct the sirens sound.  If not&amp;hellip;Bang!  Bang!  The next victim is you and you&amp;rsquo;re out of the game!&amp;#10;     In its powerful microcomputer brain electronic detective has all the suspects&amp;rsquo; alibis, plus key clues pertaining to the dastardly deed.  Its electronic I.Q. is at your fingertips!&amp;#10;     You may recheck clues at any time using the computer&amp;rsquo;s electronic memory bank.&amp;#10;     Gun shots, police sirens, and the funeral dirge are all part of the game&amp;rsquo;s play.&amp;#10;     May be played at 3 different levels: &amp;ldquo;Gumshoe,&amp;rdquo; &amp;ldquo;Sleuth,&amp;rdquo; or &amp;ldquo;Master Detective.&amp;rdquo;&amp;#10;     Automatically switches off after game play is completed.&amp;#10;     Battery operated - 6 AA &amp;ndash; you can play it anywhere.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
